  "answer": "**Kātyāyana Smṛti, Chapter 75** enumerates woman's property (*strīdhana*) as six-fold.[^1] Within this classification, *pādavandanika*—a gift for bowing at the feet of one's mother-in-law or father-in-law—is grouped with what is given out of affection (*prītidatta*).[^2]\n\n[^1]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, [Chapter 75, p-b8596e](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/75/translation/#p-b8596e).\n\n[^2]: Kātyāyana Smṛti, [Chapter 75, p-e0c275](/works/unknown-katyayana-smrti-1e06d2/75/translation/#p-e0c275).",
